  "system": {
    "description": "<p>The caster can whisper messages and receive a reply with little chance of being overheard. The caster points a finger at one creature to be included in the spell effect and must mouth the words and whisper, possibly allowing the opportunity to read lips. Magical silence blocks the spell, but otherwise, as long as the caster can see the targeted creature, the message is heard. The creature who receives the message can whisper a reply that the caster hears. The spell doesn't transcend language barriers.</p>",
